HEADWORD: Plagionite
<hw>Pla"gi*o*nite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>pla`gios</grk> oblique. So called in allusion to its usually
oblique crystallization.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A sulphide of
lead and antimony, of a blackish lead-gray color and metallic
luster.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plagiostomatous</ent>⟦br⟧
